etymologies: late 17th century: from Old Norse álka ‘razorbill’

definitions: a short-winged diving seabird found in northern oceans, typically with a black head and black and white underparts.

notes.text: Family Alcidae (the auk family), which comprises the guillemots, murres, razorbills, puffins, and their relatives. See also great auk, dovekie

shortDefinitions: short-winged diving seabird found in northern oceans
